</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,1398,452,588]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,596,452,479]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alpha" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Montanocheila">
<emphasis box="[189,304,452,478]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Cheilosia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[325,507,452,478]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Montanocheila</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[528,596,452,478]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">alpha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[607,702,453,479]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be discerned from other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barkalov" authorityYear="2002" box="[1069,1251,452,478]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Montanocheila">
<emphasis box="[1069,1251,452,478]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Montanocheila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. by the combination of presence of black pilosity on lower part of parafacia (only whitish or yellowish in other species), presence of black bristles on hind margin of scutellum, in the female this combination and distinctly glossy maculae on lateral parts of tergites III–IV.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[189,1048,629,703]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,324,629,655]" box="[189,324,629,655]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,629,655]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,629,655]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,1048,676,703]" box="[189,1048,676,703]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
The specific epithet ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[436,503,676,702]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alpha">
<emphasis box="[436,503,676,702]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">alpha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ is from the Greek and refers to the first letter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
